                [usermtghome.jpg] Far-IR at the ALS Workshop
                           1999 ALS Users' Meeting
                              October 20, 1999

   This workshop will explore the possibilities of establishing a
   synchrotron-based far-infrared (far-IR) program at the ALS. Topics
   include various methods for extracting far-IR from the storage ring and
   a number of far-IR research topics that could be enhanced by such a
   beamline. Members of the IR community will have the opportunity to
   discuss their needs and the potential scientific applications for a new
   far-IR synchrotron beamline. It will begin at 9am on Wed. Oct. 20th at
   an LBL conference room to be announced.

   Program: Workshop Program.

   Summary: Workshop Summary Memo and ALS IR News #5.

   List of speakers:
   Dimitri Basov (UC San Diego)
   Bob Bosch (SRC, Wisconsin)
   John Byrd (AFRD, LBNL)
   G. Larry Carr (NSLS, BNL)
   Wayne McKinney (ALS, LBNL)
   Laszlo Mihaly (SUNY Stony Brook)
   Joseph Orenstein (UC Berkeley)
   Richard Saykally (UC Berkeley)
   Ulrich Schade (ISAS, Berlin)
   Zack Schlesinger (UC Santa Cruz)


   Registration: Please use the ALS Users' Meeting Registration Form. If
   you only want to attend this workshop (and not the rest of the Users'
   Meeting), instead of payment information you should write "Far-IR
   Workshop Only". [Yes, that means it will be free!]

   Workshop Organizers: Michael Martin and Wayne McKinney, Advanced Light
   Source.

   For more information about this workshop, contact:

